(244,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Chest-Back-Shoulder Stretch',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891810-009blastoise.png','Get on a horse stance by opening legs wider than shoulder width, slowing lowing hips towards the ground. Open both palms of your hand and bring them both up facing the sky. Then slowly bring down both arms in a nice and slow wide arc. You should feel your Chest, Back and Shoulder Stretching.'),
(245,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Topas Shoulder Stretch',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/6087/2437349-pikachu.png','Get on a horse stance by opening legs wider than shoulder width, slowing lowing hips towards the ground. Put your palms together to reach your neutral stance. Open both arms wide like an airplane and then bring them further back. After a few seconds return back to your neutral stance and repeat.'),
(246,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Wrist-Forearm Flex Stretch',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1898248-026raichu.png','Get on your knees with your palms touching the floor and your fingers facing sideways. Lean to the left for a few seconds and then switch to the right for a few seconds to stretch your Wrist and Forearm. Another variation can be done by having your fingers facing towards yourself.'),
(247,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Forearm Stretch',60,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891758-001bulbasaur.png','Extend one arm straight out in front of you with your palm facing up. Take the other hand and gently pull the fingers of your outstretched hand downward. Hold for allotted time and repeat on the other side. Keep your shoulder blades retracted throughout the movement and do not flare your shoulder forward.'),
(248,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Arm Circles Forward',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891759-002ivysaur.png','Start by standing straight with your feet shoulder width apart. Your arms should be straight out to the sides, so that your body forms a \"T\" position.  Slowly start by making small circular motions with both arms on either side. After a few repetitions of small circles, enlarge your circles and do the same amount of reps. Your end position should look the same as the start position. Breathe in and out, and release arms to the side of the body.'),
(249,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Arm Circles Backward',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891760-003venusaur.png','Start by standing straight with your feet shoulder width apart. Your arms should be straight out to the sides, so that your body forms a \"T\" position.  Slowly start by making small circular motions with both arms on either side. After a few repetitions of small circles, enlarge your circles and do the same amount of reps. Your end position should look the same as the start position. Breathe in and out, and release arms to the side of the body.'),
(250,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Shoulder-Triceps Combo Stretch Left',60,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/6087/2438704-1202149925_t.png','Take one arm and place it across the chest and with the free arm, grab the upper arm or shoulder.  Inhale, and as your exhale, pull the arm across the chest. Now place the arm that you stretched behind your back touching it and with your free arm push down on the elbow slowly.'),
(251,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Shoulder-Triceps Combo Stretch Right',60,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891762-005charmeleon.png','Take one arm and place it across the chest and with the free arm, grab the upper arm or shoulder.  Inhale, and as your exhale, pull the arm across the chest. Now place the arm that you stretched behind your back touching it and with your free arm push down on the elbow slowly.'),
(252,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Horizontal Arm Swing',90,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891763-006charizard.png','Start by standing with your feet shoulder width apart and standing tall. Holding your arms out to the side and straight bring them forward and cross over each other in one fluid motion. Return to the starting position and repeat for the desired repetitions.'),
(253,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Standing Side Bend Left',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891764-007squirtle.png','Stand upright with feet shoulder width apart. Let your arms hang by the sides. Raise your right arm overhead bending your torso to the left as far as possible. Hold this side-bent position for a few seconds.'),
(254,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Standing Side Bend Right',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891809-008wartortle.png','Stand upright with feet shoulder width apart. Let your arms hang by the sides. Raise your right arm overhead bending your torso to the right as far as possible. Hold this side-bent position for a few seconds.'),
(255,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Spinal Roll',25,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891810-009blastoise.png','Sit down at the end of the exercise pad to make sure that your back will not hit the hard floor. Draw up your knees, and bend your head down. Put your hands under your knees. You can join your hands or not depending on what is easy on you. Keeping your spine rounded, gently swing back and forth, imitating the swinging motion of a rocking chair. Don\’t straighten your spine as you will roll backward or you will find yourself lying flat on your back, unable to swing forward again. Don\'t roll back too far on your neck. Don\’t try doing the rocking exercise too slowly either. Imagine you are a rocking chair in motion.'),
(256,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Plough into Shoulder Stand with Leg Variations into Plough',105,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/6087/2437349-pikachu.png','Roll onto upper back, raising hips, supporting lower back with hands while resting on elbows (focus weight on elbows more so than shoulders and neck). Straightening legs skyward, keep shoulders, hips, and legs aligned. Perform 3 leg variations from this pose: 1) Split leg: extend legs out as far as possible for inner thigh stretch. 2) Inverted cobbler: soles of feet together, bend knees and open hips. 3) Scissor Splits: drop right leg over head with toes barely touching floor. Left leg remains straight up. Hold for 3 breaths. Repeat on other side. After completing both sides of Scissor Splits, drop feet to the floor. Final move of sequence is bending knees to ears. come out of this pose by gently unrolling from top of spine to lower spine. To intensify: Focus on spine alignment during Shoulder Stand and increasing range of motion during leg variations. (less)'),
(257,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Seated Spinal Stretch Left',35,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1898248-026raichu.png','Seated position, pull right heel into left buttock and let knees drop to floor. Place left foot on floor on right side of right knee. Reach right hand skyward, place left hand on floor directly behind you. Twist torso to left and drop right elbow to the side of left thigh. On exhale, twist torso and head to left, while driving right elbow into thigh, keeping fingers skyward. Make sure head is up. (less)'),
(258,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Seated Spinal Stretch Right',35,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891758-001bulbasaur.png','Seated position, pull right heel into left buttock and let knees drop to floor. Place left foot on floor on right side of right knee. Reach right hand skyward, place left hand on floor directly behind you. Twist torso to left and drop right elbow to the side of left thigh. On exhale, twist torso and head to left, while driving right elbow into thigh, keeping fingers skyward. Make sure head is up. (less)'),
(259,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Cat Stretch',60,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891759-002ivysaur.png','On hands and knees with hands directly beneath shoulders and knees directly under hips, round back while exhaling and drip chin to chest. Reverse move, inhaling while arching back and lifting head.'),
(260,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Glute Stretch Left',50,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891760-003venusaur.png','Lying on back and pulling knee inward, place right ankle on left thigh. Reach right arm between right and left thigh. Reach left arm on outside of left thigh. Clasp hands around left shin. Lie back and pull left knee in towards shoulder. Repeat on other side. (less)'),
(261,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Glute Stretch Right',50,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/6087/2438704-1202149925_t.png','Lying on back and pulling knee inward, place right ankle on left thigh. Reach right arm between right and left thigh. Reach left arm on outside of left thigh. Clasp hands around left shin. Lie back and pull left knee in towards shoulder. Repeat on other side. (less)'),
(262,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Wide Leg Hamstring Stretch',50,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891762-005charmeleon.png','Stand with your feet placed 3-4 feet apart, and hinge your torso forward at the hips. “Roll” your spine down and rest your hands on the floor, letting your neck & head relax. You can also cross your arms under your head and rock your head sideways.'),
(263,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Side Twist Left',60,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891763-006charizard.png','Lie on back, bend right knee, and pull heel into buttocks. Place left hand on outside of right knee and pull across body towards floor while looking right. Repeat on other side. To intensify: Keep knee and opposite hand on floor. (less)'),
(264,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Side Twist Right',60,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891764-007squirtle.png','Lie on back, bend right knee, and pull heel into buttocks. Place left hand on outside of right knee and pull across body towards floor while looking right. Repeat on other side. To intensify: Keep knee and opposite hand on floor. (less)'),
(265,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Camel',40,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891809-008wartortle.png','Kneel on the floor with the arms by your sides. The knees are hip-width apart and the toes are flat. Shift the weight more to the front of the knees and keep the spine upright. Place the palms onto the lower back either the fingertips facing up towards the shoulder blades or down towards the buttocks. Push the thighs forward slightly and inhale lift the chest and gently arch the spine. Squeeze the shoulder blades together to open the chest and only if the neck is strong release the head back. Gently press the knees down to the floor and think of lifting and lengthening the spine rather than bending backwards. If there is tension in the lower back, don\'t extend quite as far. Relax the shoulders away from the ears and soften the face. For beginners, hold this pose for 5 to 10 deep breaths. If your spine is a little more flexible, you can place the blocks to the outside of the shins facing upright. Place the hands on top of the foam blocks and gently push the hips forward coming into a deeper stretch. If the spine is quite supple and flexible, tuck the toes under and place the hands on the heels. Maintain the hips over top of the knees and the chest lifted. Only if the neck is strong, allow the head to relax back. Be sure that the thighs are perpendicular to the floor. For more advanced, point the toes to the back and continue to hold onto the heels. If you don\'t have the flexibility to keep the thighs perpendicular to the floor, modify by tucking the toes under. Maintain this pose for 5 to 10 breaths.'),
(266,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Reclining Hero Pose',60,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891810-009blastoise.png','Begin by sitting in hero pose. Either by sitting on a foam block or on the floor. The knees are a few inches apart and spread the feet about 18 inches apart until they rest beside your hips. Insure that the inner side of each calf touches the outer side of each thigh. Turn the soles of the feet towards the ceiling. Now place the hands behind the body, fingertips facing forward. Only if the quadriceps are flexible slowly lower yourself down onto the elbows. Hold the toes and only if the neck is strong and flexible relax the crown of the head backwards. Remain here for 5 to 10 deep breaths. If there is any strain in the knees raise yourself up to a modified position.'),
(267,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Quad Stretch Left',35,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/6087/2437349-pikachu.png','Sit with your right leg bent in front of you, and the left leg extended behind you. Grab and pull and hold the left leg behind you towards your back.'),
(268,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Quad Stretch Right',35,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1898248-026raichu.png','Sit with your left leg bent in front of you, and the right leg extended behind you. Grab and pull and hold the right leg behind you towards your back.'),
(269,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Bow Pose',35,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891758-001bulbasaur.png','Lie on your front with your head down. Bend your knees and reach back to grasp your ankles. Inhale and raise the ankles so only your hips and stomach touch the floor. Look up with arms extended behind you. Take 3 deep breaths, exhale and release. '),
(270,'Stretch Flex','Workout','Low Squat',45,'Mat','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891759-002ivysaur.png','Put your palms together and squat slowly till the point that your elbows meet your knees. While on this stance rock sideways slowly.'),
