(321,'Triceps, Shoulders and Chest Boost','Workout','Y Presses',40,'Weights or Bands','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891809-008wartortle.png','Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. Raise your elbows up and out to the sides, with your palms facing forwards. Quickly press your right arm up and diagonally out to the side, so it looks like half of a capital \"Y\". Carefully lower your arm back to the starting position and repeat with the other arm to complete one rep. Keep your back straight throughout the reps.'),
(322,'Triceps, Shoulders and Chest Boost','Workout','Lying Tricep Extention',55,'Weights or Bands','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891810-009blastoise.png','Lie flat on your back on a bench or floor and position your feet flat on the floor. With a dumbbell in each hand, extend your arms over head until fully extended. Your palms should face one another and your hands should be close together. Bend the elbows and lower the weights to either side of your head. Extend your arms to return to the starting position.'),
(323,'Triceps, Shoulders and Chest Boost','Workout','Side to Side Push-up',55,'NONE','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/6087/2437349-pikachu.png','Assume a push-up position. Lift and move your left arm to the  left side and then follow with your feet and right arm too. Do one push-up and then move back to the neutral position by lifting and moving your right arm to the right side and following with your feet and left arm too. Once there move to the right as you just did to reach the neutral position and do one more push-up. After this return to the neutral position and repeat.'),
(324,'Triceps, Shoulders and Chest Boost','Workout','Pour Flys',60,'Weights or Bands','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1898248-026raichu.png','Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, slight bend in the knees, abs tigh, a dumbbell/bands in each hand, and arms down by your sides with palms facing forward. Keeping a slight bend in the elbow, exhale as you lift your arms out to the side to bring the dumbbells/bands up to shoulder height, with the dumbbells/bands pointing straight up. Hold this position and rotate the dumbbells/bands so that they are parallel with the ground, then rotate them back. Inhale as you lower the dumbbells/bands back to your sides, and don\'t let the dumbbells/bands touch your thighs between reps.'),
(325,'Triceps, Shoulders and Chest Boost','Workout','Side Leaning Tricep Extentions Left',35,'Weights or Bands and Chair','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891758-001bulbasaur.png','Grab one light dumbbell/bands in your left hand with an overhand grip, and sit sideways on a chair. Lean so your torso is at about a 75-degree angle to the bench. (You don\’t have to break out the protractor here; you just want to be somewhere between 45 and 90 degrees.) Support your body with your other hand on the chair. Hold the dumbbell/bands straight up over your head, following along the same angle as the rest of your body. Lower the weight at an angle behind your head, toward the opposite ear. Pause, then return to the starting position. Keep your upper arm at the same angle throughout. Finish the set with that arm before repeating with the other.'),
(326,'Triceps, Shoulders and Chest Boost','Workout','Side Leaning Tricep Extentions Right',35,'Weights or Bands and Chair','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891759-002ivysaur.png','Grab one light dumbbell/bands in your right hand with an overhand grip, and sit sideways on a chair. Lean so your torso is at about a 75-degree angle to the bench. (You don\’t have to break out the protractor here; you just want to be somewhere between 45 and 90 degrees.) Support your body with your other hand on the chair. Hold the dumbbell/bands straight up over your head, following along the same angle as the rest of your body. Lower the weight at an angle behind your head, toward the opposite ear. Pause, then return to the starting position. Keep your upper arm at the same angle throughout. Finish the set with that arm before repeating with the other.'),
(327,'Triceps, Shoulders and Chest Boost','Workout','One Arm Push-up Left',25,'NONE','http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/13/135472/1891760-003venusaur.png','Get into a regular push-up position with your feet wider than shoulder width apart for better balance. But instead of two arms, rest your upper one arm alone, the other arm firmly behind your back folded. From this top position lower yourself slowly till your chest almost touches the floor. Keeping your abdominals tight, push with your active arm, as if you are pushing the ground away from your body. Push yourself as high as you can with your arm totally extended ideally. If you\'re having difficulties doing these use your knees to make them a little easier.'),
